{
  "stem": "12150.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That's against the Hasidic law.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so many restrictions, and-- and my father, at least, didn't know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I joined a Zionist organization in secret.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I studied Hebrew the way they speak it in Israel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I had books.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I don't remember exactly where I studied them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I couldn't bring them home, that's for sure.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They would have noticed it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So I was sort of preparing myself for [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[HEBREW] means, in Hebrew, people that go to Israel and build a Jewish homeland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Anyway, in 1938, apparently the-- Hitler rewarded-- awarded this part of Czechoslovakia to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I don't remember the reason.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They cooperated with-- with Nazi Germany.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So from 1938 on, we belonged to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Now Hungary had a party, a sort of political party.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It's called Nyilas-- N-Y-I-L-A-S.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And that specialized in bothering and torturing Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "That was their main effort, like the KKK here, years ago.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And it was legal.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It was legal.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "It was not well spoken of, but Nyilas-- they had their men in the police.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They had their men in the courts.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And so the Jews, from then-- from that day on, were oppressed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Well, I don't remember official pogroms, like the Russians had, or Poland, where they killed 200 Jews at a time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But in general, and slowly, they confiscated all Jewish businesses, or they put in Hung-- Hungarian partners, unwillingly.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And I remember clearly when people went home from shul at night, these gangs used to beat them up.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And police stood by.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They turned the other way.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember, personally, no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and they-- apparently, the leaders of that party trained in Germany, as far as I can see.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I may be wrong.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But-- and this-- and they had their own men in the police.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
